<?php 
switch($verse){
case 1:{?>Ha. Mim.<?php break;}
case 2:{?>By the Scripture which maketh plain,<?php break;}
case 3:{?>Lo! We have appointed it a Lecture in Arabic that haply ye may understand.<?php break;}
case 4:{?>And lo! in the Source of Decrees, which We possess, it is indeed sublime, decisive,<?php break;}
case 5:{?>Shall We utterly ignore you because ye are a wanton folk?<?php break;}
case 6:{?>How many a Prophet did We send among the men of old!<?php break;}
case 7:{?>And never came there unto them a Prophet but they used to mock him.<?php break;}
case 8:{?>Then we destroyed men mightier than these in prowess; and the example of the men of old hath gone ( before them ).<?php break;}
case 9:{?>And if thou ( Muhammad ) ask them : Who created the heavens and the earth, they will surely answer : The Mighty, the Knower created them;<?php break;}
case 10:{?>Who made the earth a resting place for you, and placed roads for you therein, that haply ye may find your way;<?php break;}
case 11:{?>And who sendeth down water from the sky in ( due ) measure, and We revive a dead land therewith. Even so will ye be brought forth;<?php break;}
case 12:{?>He who created all the pairs, and appointed for you ships and cattle whereupon ye ride.<?php break;}
case 13:{?>That ye may mount upon their backs, and may remember your Lord ' s favor when ye mount thereon, and may say : Glorified be He Who hath subdued these unto us, and we were not capable ( of subduing them );<?php break;}
case 14:{?>And lo! unto our Lord we are returning.<?php break;}
case 15:{?>And they allot to Him a portion of His bondmen! Lo! man is verily a mere ingrate.<?php break;}
case 16:{?>Or chooseth He daughters of all that He hath created, and honoureth He you with sons?<?php break;}
case 17:{?>And if one of them hath tidings of that which he likeneth to the Beneficent One, his countenance becometh black and he is full of inward rage.<?php break;}
case 18:{?>( Liken they then to Allah ) that which is bred up in outward show, and in dispute cannot make itself plain?<?php break;}
case 19:{?>And they make the angels, who are the slaves of the Beneficent, females. Did they witness their creation? Their testimony will be recorded and they will be questioned.<?php break;}
case 20:{?>And they say : If the Beneficent One had ( so ) willed, we should not have worshipped them. They have no knowledge whatsoever of that. They do but guess.<?php break;}
case 21:{?>Or have We given them any Scripture before ( this Quran ) so that they are holding fast thereto?<?php break;}
case 22:{?>Nay, for they say only : Lo! we found our fathers following a religion, and we are guided by their footprints.<?php break;}
case 23:{?>And even so We sent not a warner before thee ( Muhammad ) into any township but its luxurious ones said : Lo! we found our fathers following a religion, and we are following their footprints.<?php break;}
case 24:{?>( And the warner ) said : What! Even though I bring you better guidance than that ye found your fathers following? They answered : Lo! in what ye bring we are disbelievers.<?php break;}
case 25:{?>So We requited them. Then see the nature of the consequence for the rejecters!<?php break;}
case 26:{?>And when Abraham said unto his father and his folk : Lo! I am innocent of what ye worship<?php break;}
case 27:{?>Save Him Who did create me, for He will surely guide me.<?php break;}
case 28:{?>And he made It a word enduring among his seed, that haply they might return.<?php break;}
case 29:{?>Nay, but I let these and their fathers enjoy life ( only ) till there should come unto them the Truth and a messenger making plain.<?php break;}
case 30:{?>And now that the Truth hath come unto them they say : This is mere magic, and lo! we are disbelievers therein.<?php break;}
case 31:{?>And they say : If only thin Quran had been revealed to some great man of the two towns?<?php break;}
case 32:{?>Is it they who apportion their Lord ' s mercy? We have apportioned among them their livelihood in the life of the world, and raised some of them above others in rank that some of them may take labor from others; and the mercy of thy Lord is better than ( the wealth ) that they amass.<?php break;}
case 33:{?>And were it not that mankind would have become one community, We might well have appointed, for those who disbelieve in the Beneficent, roofs of silver for their houses and stairs ( of silver ) whereby to mount,<?php break;}
case 34:{?>And for their houses doors ( of silver ) and couches of silver whereon to recline,<?php break;}
case 35:{?>And ornaments of gold. Yet all that would have been but a provision of the life of the world. And the Hereafter with your Lord would have been for those who keep from evil.<?php break;}
case 36:{?>And he whose sight is dim to the remembrance of the Beneficent, We assign unto him a devil who becometh his comrade;<?php break;}
case 37:{?>And lo! they surely turn them from the way of Allah, and yet they deem that they are rightly guided;<?php break;}
case 38:{?>Till, when he cometh unto Us, he saith ( unto his comrade ) : Ah, would that between me and thee there were the distance of the two horizons, an evil comrade!<?php break;}
case 39:{?>And it profiteth you not this day, because ye did wrong, that ye will be sharers in the doom.<?php break;}
case 40:{?>Canst thou ( Muhammad ) make the deaf to hear, or canst thou guide the blind or him who is in error manifest?<?php break;}
case 41:{?>And if We take thee away, We surely shall take vengeance on them,<?php break;}
case 42:{?>Or ( if ) We show thee that wherewith We threaten them; for lo! We have complete command of them.<?php break;}
case 43:{?>So hold thou fast to that which is inspired in thee. Lo! thou art on a right path.<?php break;}
case 44:{?>And lo! it is in truth a Reminder for thee and for thy folk; and ye will be questioned.<?php break;}
case 45:{?>And ask those of Our messengers whom We sent before thee : Did We ever appoint gods to be worshipped beside the Beneficent?<?php break;}
case 46:{?>And verily We sent Moses with Our revelations unto Pharaoh and his chiefs, and he said : I am a messenger of the Lord of the Worlds.<?php break;}
case 47:{?>But when he brought them Our tokens, behold! they laughed at them.<?php break;}
case 48:{?>And every token that We showed them was greater than its sister ( token ), and we grasped them with the torment, that haply they might turn again.<?php break;}
case 49:{?>And they said : O wizard; Entreat thy Lord for us by the pact that He hath made with thee. Lo! we verily will walk aright.<?php break;}
case 50:{?>But when We eased them of the torment, behold! they broke their word.<?php break;}
case 51:{?>And Pharaoh caused a proclamation to be made among his people saying : O my people! Is not mine the sovereignty of Egypt and these rivers flowing under me? Can ye not then discern?<?php break;}
case 52:{?>I am surely better than this fellow, who is despicable, and can hardly make ( his meaning ) plain!<?php break;}
case 53:{?>Why, then, have armlets of gold not been set upon him, or angels sent along with him?<?php break;}
case 54:{?>Thus he persuaded his people to make light ( of Moses ), and they obeyed him. Lo! they were a wanton folk.<?php break;}
case 55:{?>So, when they angered Us, We punished them and drowned them every one.<?php break;}
case 56:{?>And We made them a thing past, and an example for those after ( them ).<?php break;}
case 57:{?>And when the son of Mary is quoted as an example, behold! the folk laugh out,<?php break;}
case 58:{?>And say : Are our gods better, or is he? They raise not the objection save for argument. Nay! but they are a contentious folk.<?php break;}
case 59:{?>He is nothing but a slave on whom We bestowed favor, and We made him a pattern for the Children of Israel.<?php break;}
case 60:{?>And had We willed We could have set among you angels to be viceroys in the earth.<?php break;}
case 61:{?>And lo! verily there is knowledge of the Hour. So doubt ye not concerning it, but follow Me. This is the right path.<?php break;}
case 62:{?>And let not Satan turn you aside. Lo! he is an open enemy for you.<?php break;}
case 63:{?>When Jesus came with clear proofs ( of Allah ' s sovereignty ), he said : I have come unto you with wisdom, and to make plain some of that concerning which ye differ. So keep your duty to Allah, and obey me.<?php break;}
case 64:{?>Lo! Allah, He is my Lord and your Lord. So worship Him. This is a right path.<?php break;}
case 65:{?>But the factions among them differed. Then woe unto those who do wrong from the doom of a painful day.<?php break;}
case 66:{?>Await they aught save the Hour, that it shall come upon them suddenly, when they know not?<?php break;}
case 67:{?>Friends on that day will be foes one to another, save those who kept their duty ( to Allah ).<?php break;}
case 68:{?>O My slaves! For you there is no fear this day, nor is it ye who grieve;<?php break;}
case 69:{?>( Ye ) who believed Our revelations and were self surrendered,<?php break;}
case 70:{?>Enter the Garden, ye and your wives, to be made glad.<?php break;}
case 71:{?>Therein are brought round for them trays of gold and goblets, and therein is all that souls desire and eyes find sweet. And ye are immortal therein.<?php break;}
case 72:{?>This is the Garden which ye are made to inherit because of what ye used to do.<?php break;}
case 73:{?>Therein for you is fruit in plenty whence to eat.<?php break;}
case 74:{?>Lo! the guilty are immortal in hell ' s torment.<?php break;}
case 75:{?>It is not relaxed for them, and they despair therein.<?php break;}
case 76:{?>We wronged them not, but they it was who did the wrong.<?php break;}
case 77:{?>And they cry : O master! Let thy Lord make an end of us. He saith : Lo! here ye must remain.<?php break;}
case 78:{?>We verily brought the Truth unto you, but ye were, most of you, averse to the Truth.<?php break;}
case 79:{?>Or do they determine any thing ( against the Prophet )? Lo! We ( also ) are determining.<?php break;}
case 80:{?>Or deem they that We cannot hear their secret thoughts and private confidences? Nay, but Our envoys, present with them, do record.<?php break;}
case 81:{?>Say ( O Muhammad ) : The Beneficent One hath no son. I am first among the worshippers.<?php break;}
case 82:{?>Glorified be the Lord of the heavens and the earth, the Lord of the Throne, from that which they ascribe ( unto Him )!<?php break;}
case 83:{?>So let them flounder ( in their talk ) and play until they meet the Day which they are promised.<?php break;}
case 84:{?>And He it is Who in the heaven is God, and in the earth God. He is the Wise, the knower.<?php break;}
case 85:{?>And blessed be He unto Whom belongeth the Sovereignty of the heavens and the earth and all that is between them, and with Whom is knowledge of the Hour, and unto Whom ye will be returned.<?php break;}
case 86:{?>And those unto whom they cry instead of Him possess no power of intercession, saving him who beareth witness unto the Truth knowingly.<?php break;}
case 87:{?>And if thou ask them who created them, they will surely say : Allah. How then are they turned away?<?php break;}
case 88:{?>And he saith : O my Lord! Lo! those are a folk who believe not.<?php break;}
case 89:{?>Then bear with them ( O Muhammad ) and say : Peace. But they will come to know.<?php break;}
}?>